jDoctest
~~~~~~~~

jDoctest is an useful test library for JavaScript that inspired by
`Python`_'s `doctest`_ module. It finds testable examples within your
JavaScript files and checks if each examples runs successfully.

No more you need separated test files or documentation files. You need *a
single file* which contains an executable source code, documentations, testable
examples.

.. _Python: http://python.org/
.. _doctest: http://docs.python.org/library/doctest.html

